## **Steps to Build the React Todo App**

1. Initial Setup  
   1. Created a new React application using Create React App  
   2. Initialized the project with necessary dependencies  
   3. Set up the basic project structure  
2. Dependencies Installation  
   1. Added React and React DOM  
   2. Installed react-icons for the delete icon  
   3. Set up react-scripts for development tools  
3. Component Development  
   1. Created the main App component  
   2. Implemented useState hooks for managing todos and input  
   3. Set up the basic UI structure with a title and todo list  
4. Todo Functionality Implementation  
   1. Added ability to create new todos  
   2. Implemented todo deletion feature  
   3. Created toggle functionality for marking todos as complete  
   4. Added input form for new todos  
5. Styling  
   1. Implemented a clean, modern UI design  
   2. Added gradient background  
   3. Created styled components for todos and buttons  
   4. Implemented hover effects and transitions  
   5. Added checkmark and delete icons  
6. Testing Setup  
   1. Basic test configuration included  
   2. Set up test files for components  
7. Development Environment  
   1. Configured development server  
   2. Set up hot reloading for development  
   3. Implemented build scripts for production  
8. Project Structure  
   1. Organized components and files  
   2. Set up proper file hierarchy  
   3. Configured necessary React files and folders  
9. Cursor Assistance  
   1. Used cursor to navigate through files  
   2. Helped in editing and implementing features  
   3. Assisted in organizing code structure  
10. Final Configuration  
    1. Set up production build settings  
    2. Configured deployment options  
    3. Finalized project structure and dependencies

This streamlined version shows the key steps taken to build the Todo app without the code implementations.
